text.section:
All records of the authority shall be deemed open records and subject to public inspection, unless:
The record is excluded from inspection under KRS Chapter 61;
The record includes information that would provide an unfair competitive advantage to private sector competitors providing workers' compensation coverage in the Commonwealth;
In addition to the exemption provided by KRS 61.878(1)(c)1., the record is generated by the authority, generally recognized as confidential or proprietary, and which if openly disclosed would permit an unfair commercial advantage to competitors of the authority or other entity to which the record relates; and
The record relates to a fraud investigation conducted by the authority and that does not become evidence in a criminal or civil action.
